Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editChangeStatus(25.10)                                editChangeStatus(25.10)

Name
       editChangeStatus  - Changes the DEF status of selected wires or vias to
       the specified status

Syntax
       editChangeStatus

       [-help]

       [<shield_net_name>]

       [-nets <net>+]

       -to {ROUTED | FIXED | COVER | SHIELD | NOSHIELD}

       Changes the DEF status of selected wires or vias to the specified  sta-
       tus.  Use this command to change the net status of the selected net. If
       -nets is specified with editChangeStatus, the tool changes  the  status
       of all the objects belonging to the specified nets to the status speci-
       fied with the -to parameter.

       Note:  Before  using  this  command to change the status of a wire, you
       must select the wire by either clicking it or using the editSelect com-
       mand.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editChangeStatus parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editChangeStatus

       <shield_net_name>
              Specifies the name of the net to be  shielded  by  the  selected
              wire. Use this parameter if you want to change the selected wire
              to a SHIELD for the specified net.

              Note:  You can use this parameter only if you have specified -to
              SHIELD.

       -nets <net>+
              Specifies the names of the nets for which the object  status  is
              to be changed. If -nets is specified with  editChangeStatus, the
              tool  changes the status of all the objects (regular wires, spe-
              cial wires, regular vias, and special  vias)  belonging  to  the
              specified nets to the status specified with the  -to parameter.

       -to {ROUTED | FIXED | COVER | SHIELD | NOSHIELD}
              Specifies the DEF status of the selected wires or vias after you
              issue this command. Type the status in all upper-case letters.

              Note:  You  cannot  change  a special wire to NOSHIELD status or
              change a signal wire to SHIELD status.

Examples
              * The following commands select and then freeze  the  wires  and
                vias  on the METAL1 and METAL2 layers by changing their status
                to COVER. Innovus does not delete wires or  vias  with  status
                COVER:

                editSelect -layer {METAL1 METAL2}

                editChangeStatus -to COVER

              *

                Consider the nets depicted below:

                * The  following  command  changes the status of only the wire
                  and via under net a to FIXED. The status of the wire and via
                  under net b is not changed even though net b is selected:

                  editChangeStatus -nets a -to FIXED

                * The following command changes the status of  the  wires  and
                  vias under both nets a and b to FIXED:

                  editChangeStatus -nets {a b} -to FIXED

